-- Transneft, Rosneft, Sberbank, VTB May Move: Russian Stock Market Preview
-- Stephen Bierman
-- 2010-07-26T04:50:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/transneft-rosneft-sberbank-vtb-may-move-russian-stock-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  
 Russia’s ruble-based Micex Index was little changed at
1,380.86 in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS rose 0.4 percent
to 1449.19.  
 OAO Transneft  (TRNFP RX): The state may sell shares in
Russia’s oil pipeline operator as early as next year, Reuters
reported citing unidentified people in Russia’s Finance
Ministry. The state is also considering selling shares in OAO
Rosneft, OAO Sovcomflot, VTB Group and  OAO Sberbank , Reuters
said. Transneft fell 0.58 percent to 27,757.52 in Moscow.  
 OAO Rosneft  (ROSN RX): Russia’s largest oil producer will
report second-quarter results at around 5 p.m. local time today.
Rosneft rose 4.9 percent to 199.44 rubles.  
 OAO Mechel  (MTLR RX): Russian Prime Minister  Vladimir Putin 
said he regretted criticizing the country’s largest producer of
steel-making coal over domestic prices two years ago, comments
that caused the company’s shares to tumble. Mechel rose 1.7
percent to 638.81 rubles.  
